HEADWORD: Ketine
<hw>Ke"tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Ketone</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of a series of
organic bases obtained by the reduction of certain isonitroso compounds
of the ketones. In general they are unstable oily substances having a
pungent aromatic odor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

